  <description>[University Chapel cornerstone laying, June 11, 1926. Philosophy professor James H. Tufts delivered the address at the ceremony. A box was placed inside the cornerstone. It contained: copies of letters from John D. Rockefeller regarding financial endowments and approval of a University Chapel; photographs of both Rockefeller Sr. and Jr., and University of Chicago presidents Harper, Judson, Burton, and Mason; copies of university and city publications; and coins.]</description>
